description: The sword-slashing sequel to Peace Maker is here! Three months have passed since the Ikedaya Incident that crushed the anti-shogunate rebellion--and propelled the Shinsengumi, Kyoto's now-official police, into history as Kyoto's premium peacekeeping force. But there is no rest for the peaceful: An unexpected threat to the Shinsengumi arises, and it's going to take more than mere swords to defeat this new terror on the horizon. From the creator of the bestseller Vassalord, Momo Tama, and the original samurai epic Peace Maker comes an action-packed thrill ride, filled with a thirst for redemption, intense fighting scenes, and an amazing cast of unforgettable characters.
name: Vol. 1

description: Trouble brews from within as a new military code of conduct is unveiled for the Shinshengumi. The penalty for disobedience? Seppuku--ritual suicide. So when Vice Commander Yamanami disappears and is branded a deserter, will his friends hunt him down and force him to take his deadly punishment? Meanwhile, what trickery does Suzu have planned to further complicate things? Dark times await in this volume of Peace Maker Kurogane...
name: Vol. 2

description: Feeling frustrated by his own helplessness, Tatsunosuke runs into the eccentric outlaw Sakamoto Ryoma and demands that he be given a pistol. What does Tatsunosuke think he can accomplish with the power of a gun in his hand? Is he ready for such a responsibility? Finally, Matsumoto is appalled by the poor state of most of the men, but most shocking of all is the revelation about Okita Souji’s health. What inflicts this strong warrior?
name: Vol. 3

description: Time passes, but not all wounds are healed. Tetsu's finally getting taller, and his sword skills are improving exponentially, but the Shinsengumi members face newer and greater challenges every day. And while Sakamoto Ryoma continues his own crusade to change Japan for the better, Suzu's scheme for revenge on Tetsu takes a tragic twist.
name: Vol. 4

description: Ninjas Romance = Absolute Perfect Manga! Energetic and strong-willed, Beni doesn't care if she lives or dies as long as her death will result in embarassing her arrogant father! But one day, she suddenly encounters a Kagetora, a ninja who's fallen from the sky and swears complete loyal to her -- as her bodyguard. Kagetora has time traveled from a long, long time ago, and has devoted his life to protecting Princess Beni. Little does Kagetora know that this Beni is not the real princess... Can true love and honor survive after centuries-long time warp -- in a crazy modern world?
name: Vol. 1

description: Beni convinces Kagetora to go back with her to the future--as a student! Everything is going fine until they meet a strange and mysterious classmate, Iwatsuru. As Kagetora and Beni's interest in one another blossoms, Beni's father reminds Kagetora that he is only a mere body guard and nothing more! What's worse, he reveals that he has already arranged Beni to get married to–Iwatsuru! A test of true love and courage begins...
name: Vol. 2

description: In order to save Kagetora from the treacherous Hitaki, Beni makes a deal with the devil and confesses Kagetora's true origins to Iwatsuru. While he's understandably skeptical about time-traveling rogue ninjas, Iwatsuru is savvy enough to see that if he vows to keep Kagetora unharmed, he can get what he truly wants...Beni as his own personal princess. But even Iwatsuru's motivations for his new "relationship" with Beni are much more than meets the eye. Can Kagetora, still baffled by modern society, see through Beni's strange behavior to the truth about her feelings for him?
name: Vol. 3

description: Hunky heroes, time-traveling ninjas, and a great escape... It's all inside the next hot volume of Shinobi Life!  ...When Hitaki and Iwatsuru try to abduct Beni, Kagetora saves her and threatens the two of them if they ever harm Beni again. Realizing the danger that Beni is in, Kagetora tells Beni's father that he will no longer listen to his orders, and instead he will serve Beni alone. Outraged, Beni's father fires Kagetora, and this spurs Kagetora to run away from the house--taking Beni with him!
name: Vol. 4

description: It's back to the past for Kagetora and Beni, who are desperate to finally escape her father's manipulations. But when they are separated along the journey, what will happen to Beni, who is now completely on her own, lost a long, long time ago? Kagetora desperately fights to find her once again, but in the meantime, Beni meets some surprising new companions!
name: Vol. 5

description: There's a new vigilante in town — one who steals from the rich and keeps for herself! And what is Violet's relation to Spoiler? Collecting ROBIN #170-174 and the ROBIN/SPOILER SPECIAL
name: Robin: Violent Tendencies

description: This volume takes the Dark Knight and Superman from the alleys of Gotham City to the outer reaches of Apokolips in a quest that pits them against Darkseid, Scarecrow, Killer Croc, and more!
name: Torment
